t. Unter der doppelten Perspektive von Wandel und Beharrung untersucht Toni Tholen Konzepte von Männlichkeit zwischen solitärer Existenz, Ehe, Familie und Autorschaft in Texten von R.D. Brinkmann, R. Barthes, P. Handke, W.G. Sebald, A. Gorz bis zu M. Streeruwitz und K.O. Knausgård.  aWhat is the status of the »new man«? The literature since the late 1960s reflects in diverse ways the difficult transformation of concepts of masculinity in solitary and familial ways of life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aAllgemeine Literaturwissenschaft. 4aAnglistik. 4aFamilie. 4aGender Studies. 4aGender. 4aGermanistik. 4aLiteraturwissenschaft. 4aMännlichkeit. 4aPoetik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aBritish Studies.  aFamily.  aGender Studies.  aGender.  aGeneral Literature Studies.  aGerman Literature.  aLiterary Studies.  aMasculinity.  aPoetics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2015z9783110438673oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839430729zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839430729423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839430729/original  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-DKUb2015  aZDB-23-TGPc2014d2016